My fosters of 2022! (swipe to see) 💗

2022 has been rough at times (Chai, Matcha, Leyla 👼🌈), but it has also been full of happy moments and miracles. I learned how to tube-feed kittens and helped Cocoa & Peppermint recover from Calicivirus. My most recent 5 foster kittens overcame Panleuk, an extremely deadly virus. I fostered a total of 18 cats and kittens this year and they've all found forever homes!

This is also the year when I started volunteering on surgery days at the animal shelter almost every Thursday over the Summer. I've been posting all the cats & dogs that I meet on these days on my Instagram stories.

I also just want to take this moment to say that I've been taking an extended break from fostering for the past few months. I started my first year of undergrad at college this September (as a pre-vet), so I won't be able to foster for a bit, but I definitely plan to be back soon!

And lastly, thank you to the wonderful people at @ofosa for everything that they do! 🥰

Happy New Year! 🎊

It’s been a while, but I’m back with new fosters! 🥳

Welcome mama Joyce and her 4 month old baby, Erica! Erica is sick with a congested nose, sneezes, lack of appetite and not a lot of energy. I’m currently giving her subcutaneous fluids 1-2 times daily, antibiotics, and nebulizer treatments multiple times a day to help relieve some of her congestion. Hopefully she will start to feel better soon. ♥️ #JoyceAndErica #fosterkittens

Erica is feeling better! 🥰 

After a few days of supportive care with fluids, antibiotics and nebulizer treatments, Erica is doing a lot better! Although she is still coughing and congested, she’s starting to eat by herself and she even started playing a little bit. Go Erica!! ♥️ #JoyceAndErica

Erica is mama’s little shadow. Wherever mama cat sleeps, Erica will be snuggled up with her. If mama cat uses the scratching post, she will too. When she sees mama cat asking me for cuddles, Erica will run over and start meowing for pets too. She just loves her mama. 🥺🥰 #JoyceAndErica #adoptable

Mama cat comforting Erica. 💗 Erica got spooked by the hairdryer noise and starting crying out. Mama Joyce immediately was by Erica’s side and started comforting her. 🥺

Joyce and Erica are looking for a forever home together in Portland, OR. If you are interested in adopting this bonded pair, please send me a message! #JoyceAndErica #adoptable

Erica when she was a little baby. 🥺 She was the only survivor out of all her siblings.

Mama Joyce and her kittens arrived at the animal shelter at the beginning of March. Unfortunately, all of Erica’s siblings didn’t make it as they had relatively severe Cerebellar Hypoplasia and started having seizures as they rapidly declined. Erica, our little miracle kitten, survived after lots of intensive care and now she’s all healthy and thriving. 

Throughout all of this, mama Joyce was always very caring to her kittens and she loved them so much. After everything they’ve been through together, this sweet bonded pair are now looking for someone to adopt them. My hope is for them to go to a forever home where they can stay together forever. 💗 #adoptable #JoyceAndErica

Erica when she wakes up from a nap and wants pets. She meows when she sees me and she’ll start to purr whenever I pet her. 🥰 #JoyceAndErica

If you are interested in adopting Erica and her mama, Joyce, as a bonded pair in Oregon, please send me a message! 📥 #adoptable #pdx

Caption this video! What do you think Erica is saying? 👀

Erica and her mama, Joyce, are looking for a forever home as a bonded pair in Portland, OR! If you are interested in adopting this cuddly pair, send me a message! 📥 #adoptable #JoyceAndErica

If you are looking for a sweet and cuddly pair of cats to adopt, look no further! ✨

Joyce & Erica are a mother-daughter bonded pair that are looking for a forever home and have been waiting patiently for months. Here is a little bit about them:

•Joyce is an affectionate, purring lap cat that loves to cuddle with people. She LOVES everyone she meets. 

•Erica is vocal, sweet and spunky. She’s still a kitten, so she loves to play.

•When cuddling, Joyce will put her paw on your arm to ‘hug’ you. Then she will slow-blink up at you and purr happily. She also makes biscuits with her paws.

•Erica runs up to me everyday when I get home and starts meowing to greet me and ask for pets. She communicates in meows, chirps and purrs.

•Joyce & Erica sleep cuddled up with each other. Always.

•Erica is mama’s mini-me and she follows her everywhere. They both get nervous when separated from each other and will cry out for one another.

•They are seriously the best and deserve a loving forever home where they can stay together forever.

If you are interested in adopting these two, please send me a message! 📥 

Sharing and helping to spread the word out that these two are adoptable is greatly appreciated as well. Let’s get Joyce & Erica adopted!! 💗 #JoyceAndErica #adoptable

I picked up 4 new foster kittens and they are just a little spicy (swipe to see)! 🌶🐈 

These ~5 week old kittens were found outside and brought to the UC Davis Veterinary Hospital yesterday. They probably haven’t been around humans much, so it’s understandable why they’re scared. I’m sure that with some time, care and also treats, they will warm up in no time! 🥰

If you would like to suggest a name for these kittens, comment them down below! ⬇️ 

#yolospca #fosterkittens #SpicyOctoberKittens
A little update on the spicy kittens. 🌶 They run to me and meow whenever they see me now. 🥰 #fosterkittens #SpicyOctoberKittens

The kittens have names! Meet the October babies - Casper, Pumpkin, Spice & Boo! 🍁

There were a lot of pepper-themed names that were suggested in my welcome post of these kittens. Since the kittens have turned from spicy to extremely sweet, I decided to go with different names for them. 
(Although Spice’s name is still a nod to the pepper names since she was the spiciest kitten when she first came here.) 🌶😅 

#SpicyOctoberKittens #fosterkittens

“Excuse me? Lunch is 1 minute late!” 🤨

On a more serious note, the kittens are struggling with some GI issues currently. They are vomiting, having diarrhea and losing weight. Pumpkin & Casper are both eating well and playing, but Spice & Boo started refusing to eat today. The kittens have been getting dewormer and we are starting sub-Q fluids and syringe-feeding today for Spice & Boo. #SpicyOctoberKittens

Say “meow” if you’re here! 🐈 
#SpicyOctoberKittens

How to tell the tabby trio apart:
(names are in the order of the photos!) ⬇️

🎃 Pumpkin has an orange undertone in her brown tabby fur, which gives her a warm-brown color. She also has dark stripes.

🤍 Boo is the lightest tabby out of the three. Another way to tell her apart is her eyes. She has an eye shape that makes her look like she’s perpetually worried or sad.

🍁 Spice is the littlest brown tabby with dark stripes. It was hard to get a good photo of her because all she wanted was to climb onto my leg and cuddle. She just always wants to be close to people. 🥺 

#SpicyOctoberKittens

I love you forever, Spice. 🌈

I’m sorry to share that Spice passed away sometime in the middle of last night. I found her early today morning and she was already gone. 

It’s been hard to find the words because I truly believed that this little fighter—this kitten who meowed to demand for cuddles, who was so spicy and brave to voice her opinions when she arrived, who ended up being the sweetest kitten ever—would survive and pull through.

The kittens have been battling GI issues (vomiting, diarrhea, etc.) pretty much since they’ve gotten here. Starting from early last week, Spice started refusing food and had no appetite. I immediately began daily supportive care (sub-Q fluids, anti-nausea meds, syringe-feeding and much more) for her. Throughout it all she would have little improvements here and there, but it was up and down. In the end she had even started eating a little bit on her own again. However, her body was just too weak to fight it anymore. I do not know when she passed in the night, but I wish I had been there for her. 😔

Boo, Casper and Pumpkin have also been sick, but not as sick as Spice was. We will do everything we can to get them through this. ♥️

Note: Please refrain from commenting any medical advice or opinions. The care of these kittens is closely supervised under a veterinarian. Please know that we are doing everything we can to make sure the rest of the kittens get better.

#SpicyOctoberKittens

Boo, Pumpkin & Casper are eating a lot, growing a ton and they seem to be doing better. There has been no vomiting today and everybody is alert and active. I don’t want to jinx it though, so I’m cautiously optimistic. Hopefully they’ll keep improving!🤞 #SpicyOctoberKittens

Thank you to everyone for all of your kind words yesterday. ♥️
Pumpkin in the sunlight. ✨ Her eyes are currently transitioning from blue to green. 💙💚 #SpicyOctoberKittens
Caption what you think they’re saying. 😅 #SpicyOctoberKittens

The kittens are turning 8 weeks old this week! 🎉 Usually at this time, kittens weigh around 2 pounds and are almost ready for their spay/neuter surgeries + adoption. However, these kittens are on the small side and still have some growing to do! So they’ll stay with me for a little while longer as they grow and get big & healthy. 🌱✨

If anyone near Davis, CA is interested in adopting a kitten (or two!), send me a message! 📥  #SpicyOctoberKittens
Pumpkin the kitten with a little pumpkin. 🧡 #SpicyOctoberKittens
From a scale of 1 to 10, how cute are Casper, Pumpkin & Boo? 🥹🥰 #SpicyOctoberKittens

Good morning from the October kittens! ☀️ Since the foster room gets a lot of sunshine in the morning, the kittens love to eat their breakfast and then find the warmest spot of sunshine to bask in as they wash themselves after their meal. 😌 It’s a little slice of peace before they do what kittens do best — run around and play with everything in sight. 😅 #SpicyOctoberKittens
Brought out the tiny hats and bat wings to celebrate Halloween with the kittens! 🎃🖤✨ #SpicyOctoberKittens

Cuddles before the kittens have their spay/neuter surgeries tomorrow! These babies have grown up so fast. 🥹 Sound UP for purrs! 🥰

After tomorrow, the kittens will be available for adoption. Please message me if you would like to adopt one or two of these kittens!📥 They are all very cuddly, sweet and playful.

📍Located in Davis, California (~20 minutes away from Sacramento and ~1.5 hours away from San Francisco) 

#SpicyOctoberKittens #adoptable

Lunchtime for the kittens! 😋 All 3 kittens had meet & greets in the past few days. They were on their best behavior and did so well! Adoption times are now being scheduled and they’ll all be going to their forever homes soon. 🥹🥰 #SpicyOctoberKittens

Happy adoption day to Boo! 🎉 Boo’s adopter just picked her up! She will have two new cat brothers in her forever home to play with. Her forever mama says that she has already set up a little area for Boo and got her lots of toys! Have a wonderful life, Boo. 💗 #adopted #SpicyOctoberKittens

These two are SO sweet! And to think they arrived here over a month ago, so hissy and scared after living outside on their own. 🥺 Both of them now love to purr and be cuddled. Casper also almost always cleans his siblings after mealtimes. 🥰 Make sure your sound is on for slide 3 because there are lots of purrs! #SpicyOctoberKittens

Pumpkin just got adopted! 🥳 She’s going to a home where she will have another young cat to play with and a gentle, older dog to befriend. 💗

(The videos in this post were taken a few weeks ago. Watch it with sound on for purrs & meows!)

#adopted #SpicyOctoberKittens

And just like that, the last of my three foster kittens went to his forever home. 🥹

Through almost two months of fostering the #SpicyOctoberKittens, they have far outgrown their hashtag and have turned from spicy to the sweetest, cuddliest kittens ever. 

During their time here, these kittens battled GI issues for weeks and lost their sister, Spice, to it. From late night syringe-feeding and administering sub-Q fluids for the kittens that were too sick to eat, to coordinating with the vet almost everyday, trying out probiotics and medication and dewormers and running tests to *finally* finding something that worked, seeing these kittens all healthy and loved in their forever homes makes all of it so worth it. 

Although adoptions can be bittersweet, for the most part, it is a very happy event. It is a celebration that these three made it to this day—this milestone. From being found outside as babies to fighting illnesses, they now get to be loved and spoiled in their forever home with their forever person. Have the best life, little ones. 💗

Happy New Year! 🎊 In 2023, I fostered 6 cats/kittens with the majority of them being brown tabbies. 😅 First was the mother-daughter duo Joyce & Erica that stayed with me during the Summer. Then it was the 4 spicy kittens that ended up being so sweet. We had one angel baby, Spice, that was very sick and did not make it this year. 🕊

Although I wasn’t able to foster as many kittens as I’ve had in past years, I was able to volunteer weekly on surgery days at the animal shelter throughout the Summer. If you swipe, you can see a few of the many dogs and cats that I met! 🥰

All of the cats and dogs pictured here were either rescued by OFOSA or Yolo SPCA, so a BIG thank you to both shelters! Also, thank you to everyone here on this page for following along on my fostering adventures! 💗

#JoyceAndErica #SpicyOctoberKittens #fosterkittens
